{
  "texts": [
    "In short, if the perceived authority of video footage goes down, it will take the perceived authority of other forms of evidence down with it.",
    "Left unchallenged, the skeptical threat of deepfakes has the potential to reverberate widely.",
    "Notably, the skeptical threat of deepfakes does not depend on paranoia or irrationality on the part of ordinary persons.",
    "Reducing one's trust in a source of evidence is a reasonable response to actual reductions in the significance of that evidence.",
    "Deepfakes threaten to reduce the significance of evidence and may, for this reason, be understood as posing an epistemic threat."
  ]
}